                     <interp inst="def1-2433-18430821" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">GEORGE STUEART</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18430821-2433-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18430821-2433-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18430821-2433-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="stealingFromMaster"></interp> for stealing, on the <rs id="t18430821-cd-185" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18430821-2433-offence-1 t18430821-cd-185"></join>2nd of Aug</rs>., 1 half-crown; the money of <persName id="t18430821-name-1130" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1130" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1130" type="surname" value="RIX"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1130" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18430821-2433-offence-1 t18430821-name-1130"></join>John Rix</persName> and another, his masters.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1131" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1131" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1131" type="surname" value="RIX"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1131" type="given" value="NATHANIEL"></interp>NATHANIEL RIX</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in partnership with my brother, John Rix—the prisoner was in our service. In consequence of information I said to him, "Deliver up the money you have taken from the till"—he pulled out a half-crown and two shillings, and laid it on the desk, but denied having taken it from the till—I sent for his mother, and spoke to her—I think he was honest when we first had him—I am afraid he has got bad connexions.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1132" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1132" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1132" type="surname" value="PARKER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1132" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM PARKER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the prosecutor's employ. On the 2nd of Aug. I saw the prisoner walk behind the counter, and commence scraping up the paper—as he had no business there, I watched him narrowly, and saw him draw out the till—he left off scraping up the paper, and walked from behind the counter with his hand under his apron, as if he was putting something into his pocket—I called the attention of the clerk to it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DOANE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Had you been to the till? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Not for some time before—there had been customers in the shop.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1133" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1133" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1133" type="surname" value="WILLIAMS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1133" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE WILLIAMS</persName>
                  </hi>. I saw the prisoner open the till, then go a second time and open it, and put his hand in—he then shut it, and went to the other end of the shop.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184308210168"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Will you swear he did not put something into the till? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1134" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1134" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1134" type="surname" value="MAYNARD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1134" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN MAYNARD</persName>
                  </hi>. I had been at the till about five minutes before this, and when I left it there were five half-crowns and some silver in it—I went about five minutes after, and there were then but four half-crowns.</p>
